ntsync 1007 (combined 1007-1008): exclusive recv + channel-entry refcount

Combined patch — 1007 (channel exclusive recv) and 1008 (channel-entry
refcount for REPLY-vs-SEND_PI UAF) fold into one chunk because no
intermediate post-1007 snapshot exists.

1007: channel exclusive recv — close priority-inversion race in
ntsync_channel_send_pi.  Speculative boost of recv_wq.head was racing
with non-exclusive waiters (wait_event_interruptible default).  Non-head
receivers could win the entry-pop race, leaving the boosted head with
high priority + no work and the winner with low priority + actual work
— a real priority inversion.

1008: refcount channel entries to fix REPLY-vs-SEND_PI UAF.  REPLY's
wake_up_all on e->wq runs outside obj_lock; SEND_PI cleanup can free
the entry between REPLY's obj_unlock and REPLY's wake_up_all reaching
the freed wait queue.  refcount_t on channel_entry; whichever
decrement reaches 0 frees.

Regenerated 2026-05-04 from snapshot delta ntsync.c.post1006 →
ntsync.c.post1008 to replace the original 1007/1008 .patch files.

